## 6. i18n (9 Languages)

```typescript
import { useI18n } from '@/lib/i18n'

const { t, locale, setLocale } = useI18n()

// ✅ Type-safe
<Text>{t('reading_detail_title')}</Text>

// Adding a new key:
// 1. locales/en.ts: { new_key: 'English text' }
// 2. Copy to all 8 files (zh, zh-Hant, ko, ja, de, es, vi, th)
// 3. Use t('new_key')
```

---

## 7. Native Modules & EAS Build

```bash
# ✅ Correct — Expo resolves SDK 54 compatible version
cd apps/hexastral-app
npx expo install expo-camera

# ❌ Wrong — may install SDK 55+ → native module crash
bun add expo-camera@latest

# Build
eas build --profile production --platform ios
eas submit --platform ios
```

---

## 8. File Naming

| Type | Format | Example |
|------|--------|---------|
| Components | PascalCase | `ReadingCard.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase | `useBonds.ts` |
| Utilities | camelCase | `formatDate.ts` |
| Routes | Expo Router convention | `app/(tabs)/readings.tsx` |

---

## 9. Auth (Apple Sign-In + HMAC)

```typescript
import * as AppleAuthentication from 'expo-apple-authentication'
import * as SecureStore from 'expo-secure-store'

// Apple Sign-In → backend verify → SessionToken
const credential = await AppleAuthentication.signInAsync({ ... })
const { sessionToken } = await api.post('/auth/apple-signin', {
  identityToken: credential.identityToken,
})
await SecureStore.setItemAsync('auth_token', sessionToken)

// HMAC signs every request automatically (lib/hmac.ts)
const reading = await api.post('/bazi/compute', payload)  // ✅ auto-signed
```

---

## 10. Common Commands

```bash
# Dev
bun dev                     # Start Metro
bunx expo run:ios           # Simulator

# Build
eas build --profile production --platform ios

# Quality
bun typecheck               # TS check
bun format:fix && bun lint:fix

# Test
maestro test .maestro/flows/  # E2E

# Diagnostics (shared script; API/Workers live in other apps)
bash scripts/debug-cloudflare.sh

# If you touch hexastral-api or services/* Workers: use `bunx wrangler` from that package directory — see root `.cursorrules` §4 (do not rely on global wrangler).
```

---

